                            <comment id="44089" author="juergen.hoeller" created="Mon, 11 May 2009 03:10:39 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This is by design at present: @Controller beans are only detected in the actual DispatcherServlet context, &lt;b&gt;not&lt;/b&gt; in the root context that&apos;s loaded by ContextLoaderListener. In other words, you&apos;re supposed to define your @Controller beans in your DispatcherServlet MVC application context, with the underlying root context supposed to contain general service layer beans only.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.spring.io/browse/SPR-5368&quot; title=&quot;@Controllers deployed in the root Spring context not auto-detected by default annotation handler mapping&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SPR-5368&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;SPR-5368&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; already serves as a change request for detecting @Controllers in the root context, primarily for use with &amp;lt;context:component-scan&amp;gt;. There hasn&apos;t been a decision on this for Spring 3.0 yet. Track &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.spring.io/browse/SPR-5368&quot; title=&quot;@Controllers deployed in the root Spring context not auto-detected by default annotation handler mapping&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SPR-5368&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;SPR-5368&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; if you&apos;re interested...&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Juergen&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
